# dotfiles (chezmoi-managed macOS)

Personal + work dotfiles for `github.com/codecio/dotfiles`. Edit source under `home/`, never live `~/.foo` files.

## Architecture

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `home/` | Chezmoi source (`dot_foo` → `~/.foo`, `private_dot_ssh/` → `~/.ssh/`, `.tmpl` for templates) |
| `Brewfile` | Core dotfiles-required CLI tools only |
| `Brewfile.cli` | Daily CLI toolkit (cloud, k8s, langs, etc.) |
| `Brewfile.apps` | GUI apps (Rectangle, Slack, Spotify, …) |
| `Brewfile.archive` | Gitignored historical reference — do not resurrect or commit |
| `Makefile` | Single entry point — `make help` lists all targets |
| `.pre-commit-config.yaml` + `.gitleaks.toml` | Secret scanning (keep) |

## Conventions

- **Git identity:** path-based via `includeIf` in `dot_gitconfig.tmpl` — `~/development/*` → work, `~/home/*` and `~/dotfiles` → personal
- **Machine profile:** `home` or `work`, prompted once at `chezmoi init` (`home/.chezmoi.toml.tmpl`)

## Workflows

- Track new dotfile: `chezmoi add ~/.foo` or edit `home/` + `make apply`
- Add dotfile-required CLI: edit `Brewfile` + `make brew-bundle`
- Add daily CLI tool: edit `Brewfile.cli` + `make cli`
- Add GUI app: edit `Brewfile.apps` + `make apps`
- Apply changes: `make apply`
- Full sync: `make sync`
- Check for leaks: `make lint`

## Do NOT

- Reintroduce SOPS/age/Bitwarden — removed intentionally; discuss before adding encryption
- Commit `Brewfile.archive` (gitignored)
- Add work hostnames, IPs, employer names, or fleet details to committed files (public repo)
- Edit `~/.zshrc`, `~/.gitconfig`, or other live home files — edit `home/` source + `make apply`
- Add daily CLI tools or GUI apps to `Brewfile` — use `Brewfile.cli` or `Brewfile.apps` instead

## Before commit

```bash
make lint    # gitleaks, detect-secrets, yaml, EOF, whitespace
make apply   # verify chezmoi templates parse
```

